<?php include 'include/header.php' ?>
	<div id="content" class="bgnavcolor">
        <?php include 'include/sidebar.php' ?>
        <div id="main_content" class="white" width="760">
        	<h1>FAQs : Minors and Honours</h1>
            <div class="content_text">
		<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on">
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Minors&nbsp;and&nbsp;Honours&nbsp;</b><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</b><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Minor: &nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br /></span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Minor&nbsp;&nbsp;is&nbsp;&nbsp;an&nbsp;&nbsp;additional&nbsp;&nbsp;credential&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;student&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;earn&nbsp;&nbsp;if&nbsp;&nbsp;s/he&nbsp;&nbsp;does&nbsp;&nbsp;30&nbsp;&nbsp;credits&nbsp;&nbsp;worth&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">additional&nbsp;&nbsp;learning&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;discipline&nbsp;&nbsp;other&nbsp;&nbsp;than&nbsp;&nbsp;her/his&nbsp;&nbsp;major&nbsp;&nbsp;discipline&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;B.Tech&nbsp;&nbsp;degree.&nbsp;&nbsp;All&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">academic&nbsp;units&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;Institute&nbsp;will&nbsp;offer&nbsp;minors&nbsp;in&nbsp;their&nbsp;disciplines,&nbsp;and&nbsp;will&nbsp;prescribe&nbsp;what&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">set&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;courses&nbsp;&nbsp;and/or&nbsp;&nbsp;other&nbsp;&nbsp;activities&nbsp;&nbsp;like&nbsp;&nbsp;projects&nbsp;&nbsp;is&nbsp;&nbsp;necessary&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;earning&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;that&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">discipline. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">A&nbsp;&nbsp;student&nbsp;&nbsp;does&nbsp;&nbsp;not&nbsp;&nbsp;pre-register&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor.&nbsp;&nbsp;S/he&nbsp;&nbsp;accumulates&nbsp;&nbsp;credits&nbsp;&nbsp;by&nbsp;&nbsp;registering&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">required&nbsp;courses,&nbsp;and&nbsp;if&nbsp;the&nbsp;requirements&nbsp;for&nbsp;a&nbsp;particular&nbsp;minor&nbsp;are&nbsp;met&nbsp;within&nbsp;the&nbsp;prescribed&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">minimum&nbsp;time&nbsp;limit&nbsp;for&nbsp;the&nbsp;course,&nbsp;the&nbsp;minor&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;awarded.&nbsp;This&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Degree&nbsp;Certificate&nbsp;as&nbsp;“Bachelor&nbsp;of&nbsp;Technology&nbsp;in&nbsp;xxx&nbsp;with&nbsp;Minor&nbsp;in&nbsp;yyy.”&nbsp;The&nbsp;fact&nbsp;will&nbsp;also&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">be&nbsp;reflected&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;transcript,&nbsp;&nbsp;along&nbsp;with&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;list&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;courses&nbsp;taken&nbsp;Since&nbsp;the&nbsp;number&nbsp;of&nbsp;seats&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">available&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;each&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;courses&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;always&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;limited,&nbsp;&nbsp;one&nbsp;&nbsp;has&nbsp;&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;compete&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;place&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">every&nbsp;course.&nbsp;Maintaining&nbsp;a&nbsp;high&nbsp;academic&nbsp;standing&nbsp;therefore&nbsp;is&nbsp;essential&nbsp;for&nbsp;completing&nbsp;all&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">the&nbsp;&nbsp;requirements&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor&nbsp;&nbsp;as&nbsp;&nbsp;mentioned&nbsp;&nbsp;earlier.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even&nbsp;&nbsp;if&nbsp;&nbsp;one&nbsp;&nbsp;specified&nbsp;&nbsp;course&nbsp;&nbsp;cannot&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">earned&nbsp;during&nbsp;the&nbsp;course&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;programme,&nbsp;that&nbsp;minor&nbsp;will&nbsp;not&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;awarded.&nbsp;The&nbsp;individual&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">course&nbsp;credits earned however&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;reflected in&nbsp;the transcript.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">For&nbsp;the&nbsp;award&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;minor,&nbsp;all&nbsp;requirements&nbsp;towards&nbsp;the&nbsp;basic&nbsp;degree&nbsp;and&nbsp;the&nbsp;minor&nbsp;have&nbsp;to&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">be&nbsp;completed within the&nbsp;stipulated minimum period of&nbsp;the programme&nbsp;one&nbsp;is registered for.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Minor&nbsp;option&nbsp;is&nbsp;not&nbsp;available&nbsp;to&nbsp;Dual&nbsp;Degree&nbsp;students&nbsp;unless&nbsp;they&nbsp;have&nbsp;Academic&nbsp;standing&nbsp;1&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">(CPI &gt; 8)&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />Take&nbsp;aways&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;You do not register for a&nbsp;minor&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;A department releases a list&nbsp;of courses prescribed&nbsp;as minor courses&nbsp;every&nbsp;semester&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;If&nbsp;you complete&nbsp;at-least 30 credits in a department,&nbsp;you&nbsp;get&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor degree&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;Every&nbsp;semester,&nbsp;&nbsp;you&nbsp;compete&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;get&nbsp;these&nbsp;courses;&nbsp;allocation&nbsp;is&nbsp;done&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;basis&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">your&nbsp;CORE CPI&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">5.&nbsp;&nbsp;If&nbsp;&nbsp;you&nbsp;&nbsp;complete&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor&nbsp;&nbsp;(5&nbsp;&nbsp;courses),&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor&nbsp;&nbsp;CPI&nbsp;&nbsp;is&nbsp;&nbsp;calculated&nbsp;&nbsp;separately&nbsp;&nbsp;from&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">main&nbsp;&nbsp;Core&nbsp;&nbsp;CPI.&nbsp;&nbsp;You&nbsp;&nbsp;also&nbsp;&nbsp;received&nbsp;&nbsp;an&nbsp;&nbsp;overall&nbsp;&nbsp;CPI&nbsp;&nbsp;based&nbsp;&nbsp;on&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;credits&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;all&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">courses which&nbsp;you have&nbsp;done. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">6.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even&nbsp;&nbsp;if&nbsp;&nbsp;you&nbsp;&nbsp;do&nbsp;&nbsp;five&nbsp;&nbsp;(or&nbsp;&nbsp;less)&nbsp;&nbsp;courses&nbsp;&nbsp;not&nbsp;&nbsp;leading&nbsp;&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;a&nbsp;&nbsp;minor,&nbsp;&nbsp;these&nbsp;&nbsp;courses&nbsp;&nbsp;are&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">mentioned in the transcript, along&nbsp;with the&nbsp;grade&nbsp;you got in them.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</b><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</b><br />
<br />
<hr style="text-align: -webkit-auto;" />
<a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=343163481959826682" name="2" style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"></a><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Honours :<br /></b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Honours is&nbsp;an additional credential a student will earn if&nbsp;s/he opts for the&nbsp;extra&nbsp;&nbsp;30 credits&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">needed for this in &nbsp;her/his own discipline. The&nbsp;concerned department specifies the&nbsp;course&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">requirements for earning&nbsp;the Honours.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">As&nbsp;in&nbsp;the&nbsp;case&nbsp;of&nbsp;minors,&nbsp;a&nbsp;student&nbsp;does&nbsp;not&nbsp;register&nbsp;for&nbsp;Honours.&nbsp;S/he&nbsp;accumulates&nbsp;credits&nbsp;by&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">registering&nbsp;&nbsp;for&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;required&nbsp;&nbsp;courses/academic&nbsp;&nbsp;activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;On&nbsp;&nbsp;successful&nbsp;&nbsp;accumulation&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">credits&nbsp;&nbsp;at&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;end&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;programme,&nbsp;&nbsp;this&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;mentioned&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;Degree&nbsp;&nbsp;Certificate&nbsp;&nbsp;as&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">“Bachelor&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;Technology&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;xxx,&nbsp;&nbsp;with&nbsp;&nbsp;Honours.”&nbsp;&nbsp;The&nbsp;&nbsp;fact&nbsp;&nbsp;will&nbsp;&nbsp;also&nbsp;&nbsp;be&nbsp;&nbsp;reflected&nbsp;&nbsp;in&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">transcript, along&nbsp;with the&nbsp;list of courses, etc., taken. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">For&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;award&nbsp;&nbsp;of&nbsp;&nbsp;the&nbsp;&nbsp;honours&nbsp;&nbsp;to&nbsp;&nbsp;B.Tech&nbsp;&nbsp;and&nbsp;&nbsp;Integrated&nbsp;&nbsp;M.Sc.&nbsp;&nbsp;students,&nbsp;&nbsp;all&nbsp;&nbsp;requirements&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">towards the&nbsp;basic degree&nbsp;and the honours&nbsp;have&nbsp;to&nbsp;be&nbsp;completed&nbsp;within the&nbsp;stipulated period of&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">the programme&nbsp;one&nbsp;is registered for.&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</b><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Take&nbsp;aways&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;An honor&nbsp;is exactly&nbsp;like&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor except in that all&nbsp;honor&nbsp;courses&nbsp;are&nbsp;of the&nbsp;same&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">department&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;Honor&nbsp;courses are&nbsp;either&nbsp;advanced level courses in&nbsp;your discipline, or&nbsp;are&nbsp;courses&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">designed to&nbsp;give&nbsp;you more&nbsp;exposure&nbsp;to different areas of&nbsp;your discipline&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;DD&nbsp;students have&nbsp;to do honor&nbsp;by&nbsp;default. They&nbsp;are&nbsp;considered&nbsp;as their core&nbsp;courses.&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br /><br />FAQs&nbsp;regarding last year&nbsp;minor&nbsp;and&nbsp;honors<br /><br />1. If&nbsp;I am&nbsp;a DD&nbsp;student&nbsp;and&nbsp;I&nbsp;want to take a minor, how&nbsp;heavy will the load&nbsp;become?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">First, the&nbsp;CPI&nbsp;threshold is 8&nbsp;without&nbsp;backlogs for&nbsp;you to even take&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor. Doing&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">both will&nbsp;be&nbsp;difficult, because it will mean&nbsp;you have&nbsp;to&nbsp;take&nbsp;6 courses semester&nbsp;after&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">semester.&nbsp;It might be easier&nbsp;to take&nbsp;less than 5&nbsp;electives (essentially&nbsp;forgoing&nbsp;your&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">minor)&nbsp;in interest areas in semesters which&nbsp;are&nbsp;slightly&nbsp;'easier'&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. How&nbsp;should&nbsp;we&nbsp;try to&nbsp;match&nbsp;our&nbsp;minor&nbsp;with our&nbsp;major? Which combination&nbsp;is<br />'good'?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">This depends on interest,&nbsp;aptitude and what&nbsp;you want for&nbsp;your future.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;For&nbsp;example, if&nbsp;you are&nbsp;in Electrical,&nbsp;you might want to take&nbsp;a&nbsp;MA minor to get&nbsp;your&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">mathematical basis right&nbsp;if&nbsp;you want to become&nbsp;a&nbsp;Professor&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;You might take&nbsp;a&nbsp;PH minor if&nbsp;you&nbsp;want to&nbsp;go into Microelectronics&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;You might want to take&nbsp;an ME/MG minor if&nbsp;you&nbsp;want to go into entrepreneurship&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">4. &nbsp;Keep in mind that there&nbsp;are&nbsp;no&nbsp;generally&nbsp;correct answers&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">5. &nbsp;Make&nbsp;a&nbsp;shortlist of minors&nbsp;you are&nbsp;interested in, and talk to seniors and professors in&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">each of those&nbsp;departments to know exactly&nbsp;what&nbsp;you are&nbsp;getting&nbsp;into&nbsp;</span><br />
<div style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">
<b><br /></b></div>
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. What&nbsp;is the&nbsp;structure&nbsp;of&nbsp;an&nbsp;honor?&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Honors are&nbsp;30 credits done&nbsp;in&nbsp;your own Department&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;Different departments have&nbsp;different requirements&nbsp;-&nbsp;for&nbsp;example, 5 courses,&nbsp;3 courses&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">+&nbsp;BTP, 3 courses +&nbsp; 2&nbsp;electives&nbsp;and so on&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;Otherwise, the&nbsp;structure&nbsp;is the same&nbsp;as that of&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />4. If&nbsp;I am&nbsp;a DD&nbsp;student,&nbsp;can&nbsp;I do a minor&nbsp;in&nbsp;my&nbsp;final year&nbsp;(9th&nbsp;and&nbsp;10th semesters)?&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;As of&nbsp;now, this&nbsp;is not allowed, since&nbsp;the student is expected to focus on his/her&nbsp;DDP&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">in the&nbsp;final&nbsp;year&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />5. What&nbsp;is an&nbsp;audit course?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;An audit&nbsp;is a&nbsp;sit-through,&nbsp;zero credit&nbsp;course&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;You need to attend it like&nbsp;any&nbsp;normal course,&nbsp;get 80% attendance&nbsp;and&nbsp;give the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">examinations prescribed&nbsp;by&nbsp;the instructor&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />6. If&nbsp;I do&nbsp;not&nbsp;take&nbsp;a minor, and&nbsp;do 5 unconnected-by-department courses instead, how<br />can&nbsp;this benefit me?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;In the&nbsp;first place,&nbsp;you should take&nbsp;these&nbsp;courses due&nbsp;to interest, so that itself is a&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">benefit, since&nbsp;you will&nbsp;be&nbsp;interested in the&nbsp;course&nbsp;from the beginning&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;Further,&nbsp;you&nbsp;can tailor&nbsp;your&nbsp;application/resume by&nbsp;a&nbsp;clever choice&nbsp;of courses across&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">departments, so that&nbsp;you&nbsp;can project&nbsp;yourself&nbsp;as having&nbsp;specialized knowledge&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">skill&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;However,&nbsp;you won’t be&nbsp;given any&nbsp;minor degree&nbsp;(unless&nbsp;you complete&nbsp;atleast 30&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">credits in one&nbsp;single&nbsp;department) by&nbsp;the&nbsp;institute.&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />7. Say that a person&nbsp;is unable to take a minor&nbsp;course&nbsp;in&nbsp;Semester&nbsp;A&nbsp;because&nbsp;of&nbsp;a CPI<br />problem. He/she&nbsp;waits for&nbsp;a year&nbsp;and&nbsp;builds&nbsp;up&nbsp;his/her&nbsp;CPI. Can&nbsp;he/she&nbsp;do the&nbsp;minor<br />course&nbsp;of&nbsp;Semester&nbsp;A&nbsp;with his/her&nbsp;juniors?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Yes,&nbsp;you can!&nbsp;Unless there&nbsp;are&nbsp;prerequisites (do check this in the&nbsp;beginning)&nbsp;you need&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">not&nbsp;do&nbsp;your 5&nbsp;courses in&nbsp;order&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;It is possible&nbsp;to do what&nbsp;you have&nbsp;asked for&nbsp;in&nbsp;your&nbsp;question if the slots&nbsp;permit&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;And, even if&nbsp;you fail&nbsp;in one minor course, one&nbsp;mistake&nbsp;will&nbsp;not irrevocably&nbsp;damage&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">your&nbsp;prospects&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">4. &nbsp;Since&nbsp;you have&nbsp;5 minor courses and&nbsp;6 semesters to&nbsp;do them in,&nbsp;you do have&nbsp;one&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">semester in hand&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">5. &nbsp;There&nbsp;are&nbsp;options open&nbsp;even if&nbsp;you fail&nbsp;once&nbsp;</span><br />
<hr style="text-align: -webkit-auto;" />
<a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=343163481959826682" name="4" style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"></a><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">8. Can I&nbsp;take&nbsp;2 minors?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Yes, if&nbsp;you are&nbsp;a&nbsp;B.Tech&nbsp;having&nbsp;Academic&nbsp;Standing&nbsp;1 (CPI&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;8, no backlogs)&nbsp;and if&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">the slot&nbsp;permits.&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">9. Does the honours grade&nbsp;affect my CPI or&nbsp;is it just like&nbsp;the&nbsp;minor?? I'm&nbsp;a&nbsp;B.Tech<br />student.&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;For&nbsp;B.Techs, the&nbsp;honor&nbsp;CPI&nbsp;is, like the&nbsp;minor CPI,&nbsp;distinct from the core&nbsp;CPI.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;In the&nbsp;case&nbsp;that&nbsp;you complete&nbsp;the 30 credits of&nbsp;your&nbsp;honor, an honor&nbsp;CPI&nbsp;will be&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">separately&nbsp;calculated and&nbsp;entered separately&nbsp;in&nbsp;your&nbsp;final transcript.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;In the&nbsp;case&nbsp;that&nbsp;you do not complete&nbsp;your honor&nbsp;(for&nbsp;example,&nbsp;you do 2&nbsp;extra&nbsp;courses&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">in&nbsp;your Department), the&nbsp;grades of these&nbsp;courses will appear separately, but&nbsp;there&nbsp;will&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">be&nbsp;no honor&nbsp;CPI; these&nbsp;grades will&nbsp;also not be used to calculate the&nbsp;core&nbsp;CPI.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">However, for&nbsp;DD student, honor courses&nbsp;are&nbsp;a&nbsp;part&nbsp;of&nbsp;core&nbsp;and it&nbsp;will&nbsp;be&nbsp;added in&nbsp;your CPI.&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">10. Is an&nbsp;honours beneficial&nbsp;even&nbsp;if&nbsp;one&nbsp;doesn't&nbsp;want to do research&nbsp;or&nbsp;further&nbsp;study.&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Yes. A few possible&nbsp;cases (not comprehensive) are&nbsp;below:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;You want focussed knowledge&nbsp;in&nbsp;your department&nbsp;to take&nbsp;a&nbsp;job in a&nbsp;certain&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">specialized area, so that&nbsp;you can compete&nbsp;with, say,&nbsp;an MTech who has specialized in&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">the same area&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;You want to do a&nbsp;job in&nbsp;a&nbsp;field different from that&nbsp;which&nbsp;you&nbsp;are&nbsp;studying&nbsp;in&nbsp;your&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">department, but&nbsp;which requires similar&nbsp;(for&nbsp;example, quantitative)&nbsp;skills. You might&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">like&nbsp;to show extremely&nbsp;strong&nbsp;skills by&nbsp;completing an honor&nbsp;successfully, thereby&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">differentiating&nbsp;yourself from&nbsp;a&nbsp;batchmate who has&nbsp;not done that honor&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">11. If&nbsp;I couldn't get a minor&nbsp;course&nbsp;from&nbsp;a certain&nbsp;department&nbsp;through&nbsp;centralized&nbsp;cpi-<br />based allotment, but in case&nbsp;the&nbsp;instructor&nbsp;allows me&nbsp;to join&nbsp;the&nbsp;course&nbsp;as a credit<br />course, Will the credits of&nbsp;the&nbsp;course&nbsp;be&nbsp;considered&nbsp;while&nbsp;me&nbsp;being considered&nbsp;for&nbsp;a<br />"minor"&nbsp;from&nbsp;that&nbsp;department at the&nbsp;end&nbsp;of&nbsp;4 years?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;According&nbsp;to the&nbsp;rules, entry&nbsp;to a&nbsp;course&nbsp;offered as a minor course&nbsp;should&nbsp;be&nbsp;only&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">through centralized CPI-based allotment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;Thus, if&nbsp;you want to take&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor-offered&nbsp;course&nbsp;as a credit&nbsp;course&nbsp;with only&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">permission of the&nbsp;instructor, this is&nbsp;technically&nbsp;not&nbsp;allowed. You will&nbsp;have&nbsp;to approach&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">the Dean AP; each request will&nbsp;be&nbsp;treated on a&nbsp;case-to-case&nbsp;basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />12. I have&nbsp;Academic Standing I&nbsp;but minor&nbsp;courses are&nbsp;run&nbsp;in&nbsp;only slot&nbsp;5 so can&nbsp;I actually<br />do two minor&nbsp;courses per&nbsp;semester? If&nbsp;yes, how?&nbsp;</b><br />
<hr style="text-align: -webkit-auto;" />
<a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=343163481959826682" name="5" style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"></a><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Two&nbsp;possible cases:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;We&nbsp;will&nbsp;try&nbsp;to&nbsp;run multiple&nbsp;minor courses in each&nbsp;department per semester;&nbsp;2 slots&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">will&nbsp;be&nbsp;devoted to these&nbsp;minor courses. Thus, if&nbsp;you are&nbsp;doing&nbsp;2 minors,&nbsp;you can do&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">one&nbsp;in each of these&nbsp;slots&nbsp;in different Departments.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Even if we&nbsp;cannot immediately&nbsp;do the&nbsp;above, we&nbsp;could try, based on the number&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">people who want 2 minors (we&nbsp;will&nbsp;take&nbsp;feedback&nbsp;on this), to run half the&nbsp;minors&nbsp;in&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">one&nbsp;slot&nbsp;and half in another. This will&nbsp;be&nbsp;a&nbsp;huge&nbsp;logistical problem, though,&nbsp;so there&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">will&nbsp;have&nbsp;to be a&nbsp;substantial number&nbsp;of people.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;There&nbsp;is also provision of&nbsp;having&nbsp;6 to 12 credits of&nbsp;minor as a project in some&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">department, namely&nbsp;IDC, Computer Science&nbsp;and Energy.&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />13. I am&nbsp;a student of&nbsp;electrical engineering. I would&nbsp;like&nbsp;to take up&nbsp;a minor&nbsp;degree&nbsp;in<br />computer&nbsp;science, as well&nbsp;as a couple of&nbsp;courses&nbsp;that I might like&nbsp;in&nbsp;material&nbsp;science&nbsp;and<br />EP. Is this possible?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Given that&nbsp;you&nbsp;are&nbsp;a&nbsp;B.Tech,&nbsp;you can in these&nbsp;cases:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2. &nbsp;If&nbsp;your CPI&nbsp;is now above&nbsp;8 and is&nbsp;expected to stay&nbsp;above&nbsp;8,&nbsp;you can do it&nbsp;pretty&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">peacefully.&nbsp;Given that&nbsp;you want to do about 7-8 courses (5 minor +&nbsp;a&nbsp;couple&nbsp;(couple =&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2 or 3 :P))&nbsp;you&nbsp;are&nbsp;essentially&nbsp;looking&nbsp;at about 4 semesters after&nbsp;your second with 5&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">theory&nbsp;courses&nbsp;and 2 semesters with&nbsp;6 theory&nbsp;courses, which should not be&nbsp;difficult&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">with careful planning.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3. &nbsp;If&nbsp;your CPI&nbsp;is not now above&nbsp;8, work hard and&nbsp;get&nbsp;it&nbsp;above&nbsp;8 as soon as possible, so&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">that&nbsp;you will&nbsp;have&nbsp;the&nbsp;flexibility&nbsp;of doing&nbsp;1 or&nbsp;2&nbsp;extra&nbsp;courses a&nbsp;semester as and&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">you want to do them.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">14. Will the minor&nbsp;allotment be done&nbsp;on&nbsp;cpi basis&nbsp;in&nbsp;every semester&nbsp;or&nbsp;just for&nbsp;the&nbsp;first<br />time? Because&nbsp;of&nbsp;the&nbsp;difference&nbsp;in&nbsp;grading pattern&nbsp;in&nbsp;various departments it becomes<br />tough&nbsp;for&nbsp;some&nbsp;students&nbsp;to&nbsp;maintain there&nbsp;cpi.&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;The&nbsp;allotment will be done&nbsp;on CPI&nbsp;basis&nbsp;for every&nbsp;semester&nbsp;-&nbsp;that too, the&nbsp;basic CPI,&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">not the&nbsp;minor CPI.&nbsp;The&nbsp;philosophy&nbsp;is that the&nbsp;minor is something&nbsp;you do over and&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">above&nbsp;your basic&nbsp;courses. Thus, it&nbsp;is something&nbsp;that&nbsp;you need to compete&nbsp;for&nbsp;across&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">departments.&nbsp;If&nbsp;you&nbsp;cannot keep the CPI&nbsp;needed to get into a minor, it&nbsp;is seen as an&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">indication that&nbsp;you should concentrate on&nbsp;your&nbsp;core&nbsp;and develop it to become eligible.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">15. can&nbsp;we&nbsp;take&nbsp;up&nbsp;minors in&nbsp;the&nbsp;3rd&nbsp;year....... i&nbsp;am&nbsp;a&nbsp;dd&nbsp;and&nbsp;have&nbsp;a 7 point say if&nbsp;my cpi<br />improves&nbsp;to 8 in&nbsp;the&nbsp;2nd&nbsp;sem&nbsp;of&nbsp;sophie year-&nbsp;can&nbsp;i take&nbsp;a minor&nbsp;then? if&nbsp;not-&nbsp;then can&nbsp;i<br />take&nbsp;one&nbsp;at the&nbsp;start of&nbsp;3rd&nbsp;year?&nbsp;P.S.-&nbsp;completing it is totally my head-ache&nbsp;(i will over-<br />load)&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;Yes,&nbsp;you can.&nbsp;Ideally,&nbsp;you should take&nbsp;at least one&nbsp;in the&nbsp;second&nbsp;year also.&nbsp;You see,&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">overloading&nbsp;(=&nbsp;taking&nbsp;two minor courses in one&nbsp;sem) is difficult because&nbsp;all&nbsp;minor&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">courses currently&nbsp;run in the&nbsp;same&nbsp;slot&nbsp;(5).&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<hr style="text-align: -webkit-auto;" />
<a href="http://draft.blogger.com/blogger.g?blogID=343163481959826682" name="6" style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"></a><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;"><br />16. In&nbsp;an&nbsp;honors, are&nbsp;new&nbsp;courses taught or&nbsp;the&nbsp;courses of&nbsp;department&nbsp;are&nbsp;taught with<br />more&nbsp;details?&nbsp;&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1. &nbsp;In honors, advanced&nbsp;courses of the&nbsp;department (starting&nbsp;with 4, 5 or 6)&nbsp;are&nbsp;taught.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">17. What&nbsp;is the&nbsp;difference&nbsp;between&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor&nbsp;and&nbsp;an&nbsp;Institute&nbsp;Elective?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Any&nbsp;course&nbsp;running&nbsp;in the&nbsp;institute except&nbsp;your own department courses can be&nbsp;taken&nbsp;as an&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">institute elective. However, minor courses can be&nbsp;chosen&nbsp;only&nbsp;from the&nbsp;given list on&nbsp;</span><br />
<a href="http://www.iitb.ac.in/asc" style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">www.iitb.ac.in/asc.&nbsp;</a><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">If&nbsp;you want to choose&nbsp;a&nbsp;course&nbsp;given in the&nbsp;minor courses list as an&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">institute elective,&nbsp;you require&nbsp;instructor’s permission.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;</span><br />
<b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">18. &nbsp;How&nbsp;will my minor/honor&nbsp;or&nbsp;core&nbsp;CPI will appear&nbsp;in&nbsp;my transcript?&nbsp;</b><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">As of&nbsp;now,&nbsp;you will&nbsp;be&nbsp;receiving&nbsp;the&nbsp;following&nbsp;sets of CPIs in&nbsp;your transcript:&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Minor&nbsp;CPI</b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;–&nbsp;This will appear only&nbsp;if&nbsp;you have&nbsp;completed a&nbsp;minor degree.&nbsp;(if&nbsp;have&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">done&nbsp;some&nbsp;of the&nbsp;minor courses but&nbsp;not enough to acquire&nbsp;a&nbsp;minor degree, then those&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">courses would be&nbsp;counted in Additional learning&nbsp;CPI).&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">2.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Honor&nbsp;CPI</b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;–&nbsp;This will appear only&nbsp;if&nbsp;you have&nbsp;completed an honor&nbsp;degree&nbsp;(if&nbsp;have&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">done&nbsp;some&nbsp;of the&nbsp;honor&nbsp;courses but&nbsp;not enough to acquire&nbsp;a&nbsp;honor&nbsp;degree, then those&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">courses would be&nbsp;counted in Additional learning&nbsp;CPI).&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">3.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Additional learning CPI</b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;–&nbsp;This would account for&nbsp;all&nbsp;those courses&nbsp;which&nbsp;you have&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">completed but are&nbsp;not&nbsp;a&nbsp;part of&nbsp;your core, nor have&nbsp;been included in&nbsp;your minor CPI&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">(if&nbsp;you have&nbsp;acquired&nbsp;a&nbsp;degree).&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">4.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Core&nbsp;CPI</b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;–&nbsp;This would&nbsp;account for all&nbsp;of&nbsp;your&nbsp;core&nbsp;courses including&nbsp;Institute&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">elective&nbsp;and department&nbsp;elective. This CPI&nbsp;would also appear on&nbsp;your Resume for&nbsp;the&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">placement purposes.&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">5.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><b style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">Overall&nbsp;CPI</b><span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">&nbsp;–&nbsp;This CPI&nbsp;would account for all&nbsp;the&nbsp;credited courses which&nbsp;you have&nbsp;</span><br />
<span style="text-align: -webkit-auto;">completed in&nbsp;IIT&nbsp;Bombay. &nbsp;</span></div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
